Abiodun Nejo, Ado Ekiti Ekiti State Commissioner for Information, Muyiwa Olumilua, has condoled with the families of victims of a fatal auto accident that occurred along Ikere Ekiti – Ado Ekiti road on Saturday. Olumilua, who described the accident as “saddening and unfortunate,” cautioned motorists against speeding and reckless driving to prevent accidents and loss of lives. The commissioner, in a statement on Thursday, stressed that most accidents were avoidable, noting that “media reports indicated that the accident was as a result of speeding. Most accidents would have been averted if the drivers were more careful”. An 18-seater bus said to be conveying wedding guests somersaulted while on speed, leaving three passengers dead on the spot while two others among those rushed to Ekiti State University Teaching Hospital died later. Olumilua stressed the need for motorists to concentrate and keep their eyes on the road, obey traffic rules and avoid road-rage. Copyright PUNCH.
